Answer (numerical number):

The question regarding the number of atoms in 5-ethyl-3,5-dimethylhept-3-ene can be approached by considering the molecular structure and utilizing knowledge of organic chemistry. 

To determine the total number of atoms in the compound, one must analyze the molecular formula, which provides information on the types and quantities of atoms present in the molecule. In this case, the molecular formula of 5-ethyl-3,5-dimethylhept-3-ene is C11H22, indicating that the molecule consists of 11 carbon atoms and 22 hydrogen atoms.

Therefore, the total number of atoms in 5-ethyl-3,5-dimethylhept-3-ene is 11 + 22 = 33 atoms.
